title.narrative: Field Offices have increased capacity to manage subnational programming in UNICEF South Sudan

description.narrative: UNICEF and partners' humanitarian and aligned development action kept women and children affected by food insecurity, displacement, conflict, disease outbreaks and climatic shocks alive and thriving, safe and learning. 289,512 Individuals and 59,114 children under five in hard-to-reach locations were reached with services through joint integrated rapid response missions (IRRMs) with WFP and FAO. UNICEF progressed the agenda for children within a regular programme adequately informed by risk and ensured efficient operation of a coordinated response across the country. Minimum preparedness actions (93% score) by UNICEF including its 13 Field Offices and partners facilitated readiness for predictable action. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/02/2020
